      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHITE MOCHA (8) finished seventh last time at Sandown but could not have been more impressive a few runs back in her quick 34.20 win at Sandown over 595m. Should be in this for a long way. BALDING SANDY (2) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing eighth (38.51) in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from five starts. Key player if finds best. SEGER (6) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Warrnambool behind Mepunga Rule (38.10) in a Restricted WIN. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form from his last run stacks up well. Can feature again. JUST IN CASEY (3) must be respected at her pet distance.",
